{"lemma":"ذَرِبٍ","slug":"ذَرِبٍ","root":"ذ.ر.ب","root_slug":"ذ-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13753","n13754","n13756","n13757","n13758","n13759","n13760"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13753","headword_ar":"ذَرِبَ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabN","text_ar":"ذَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araAbapN","text_ar":"ذَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, A, K,) said of a sword, and a spear-head, (A,) or of a thing (M, Msb) of any kind, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penetrating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or, said of a sword, and of a spear-head, it signifies [or signifies also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was steeped in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imbued with, poison."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba lisaAnuhu","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ لِسَانُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, [and so the inf. n.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His tongue was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly speaking, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp in the extremity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and also tropically, i. e., in a good sense, as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent; without barbarousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impediment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in a bad sense, as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profuse of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorous: bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt: foul, unseemly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cared not what he said."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [For]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabN","text_ar":"ذَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araAbapN","text_ar":"ذَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the tongue [properly speaking, or, as is said in the A, tropically]: (S, M, A, TA:) and the former, (TA,) or the latter, (Msb,) [or each.] metaphorically, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chasteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; (Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without barbarousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impediment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a quality approved: and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profuseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; a quality disapproved: (TA:) and the former, [or each,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"badness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruptness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (M, K:) and the former, (AZ, S, M, K,) or the latter, (Msb,) or each, (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscenity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (AZ, S, M, A, Msb, K:) and the pl. of the former [used as a simple subst.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oraAbN","text_ar":"اَذْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AZ, IAar, S, M, K.) A poet says, (S,) namely, Hadramee Ibn-'Ámir El-Asadee, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaqado Tawayotukumu EalaY bulalaAtikumo\n                      \n                     \n                        wa Earafotu maA fiykumo mina AlA^a*oraAbi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I have borne with you not withstanding your vices and evil actions, and have known what is in you of foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, qualities of the tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (AZ, S:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY bulalaAtikumo","text_ar":"على بُلَلَاتِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, TA) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notwithstanding what is in you of annoyance and enmity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but accord. to Th, he said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEoyaAbi","text_ar":"الاَعْيَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayobN","text_ar":"عَيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) [Accord. to Z,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhimo A^a*oraAbN","text_ar":"فِيهِمْ اَذْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In them are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities that are"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causes of evil, corruption, wrong, injury,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribato maEidatuhu","text_ar":"ذَرِبَتْ مَعِدَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabN","text_ar":"ذَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araAbapN","text_ar":"ذَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uruwbapN","text_ar":"ذُرُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His stomach was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keen, by reason of hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M; but only the first of the inf. ns. of the verb in this sense, and not the verb itself, is there mentioned:) [or] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his stomach was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K; but only the inf. ns. of the verb in this sense, and in the next, and not the verb itself, is there mentioned:) and also, (M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his stomach was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, Msb, K:) thus having two contr. significations. (M, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba AljuroHu","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ الجُرْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabN","text_ar":"ذَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound admitted not of cure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state, and wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and admitted not of cure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiyd","text_ar":"صَدِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ichor tinged with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba A^anofuhu","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ اَنْفُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araAbapN","text_ar":"ذَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His nose dripped; let fall drops."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araba","text_ar":"ذَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2, in two places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabotu","text_ar":"ذَرَبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I excited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provoked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exasperated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":959},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaDoribu bayonanaA waya*oribu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَضْرِبُ بَيْنَنَا وَيَذْرِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one makes a separation between us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and excites discord:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya*oribu","text_ar":"يَذْرِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is perhaps here used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya*orubu","text_ar":"يَذْرُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to assimilate it to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaDoribu","text_ar":"يَضْرِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","Msb","K","S","TA","AZ","IAar","T"]},{"entry_id":"n13754","headword_ar":"ذرّب","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*oriybN","text_ar":"تَذْرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sharpened"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, S, K) an iron instrument [such as a sword and a spear-head &c.]; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araba","text_ar":"ذَرَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, Msb, TA,) accord. to the K"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is without any other authority, and contr. to analogy, as neither its third nor its second letter is a faucial, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arobN","text_ar":"ذَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*rb","text_ar":"اذرب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KL.) Also, inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poisoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sword, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steeped"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in poison, and, when it was well steeped, took"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth and sharpened"},{"kind":"text","text":"it; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araba","text_ar":"ذَرَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise, is allowable. (T, TA.)       -A2-  The inf. n. also signifies A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holding"},{"kind":"text","text":"her infant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that it may satisfy its want"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by evacuation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the words in the explanation ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY yaqoDiYa HaAjatahu","text_ar":"حَتَّى يَقْضِىَ حَاجَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") commonly mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as Freytag supposes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by sucking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","Msb","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13756","headword_ar":"ذَرْبٌ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK and in a MS copy of the K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so accord. to the TA, [which is followed by the TK, and so in my MS copy of the K, but altered from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arobN","text_ar":"ذَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I incline to think the right reading,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shoemaker's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izomiyl","text_ar":"اـِزْمِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word well known as signifying his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knife, with which he cuts the leather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but here explained in the TA as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$ofaY","text_ar":"اـِشْفَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which he sews"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13757","headword_ar":"ذُرْبٌ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an irreg. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13758","headword_ar":"ذِرْبٌ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gud~apN","text_ar":"غُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ganglion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (AZ, T:) or so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irobapN","text_ar":"ذِرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing that is sometimes in the neck of a human being"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a beast, like a pebble:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the former word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain disease in the liver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slow of cure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irabN","text_ar":"ذِرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irabapN","text_ar":"ذِرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T,) or this latter is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irobapN","text_ar":"ذِرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","T","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13759","headword_ar":"ذَرَبٌ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. passim]. (T, S, M, &c.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arabay~aA","text_ar":"ذَرَبَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see there a pl. or a dual form, in three places. ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An incurable disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [in the present day applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diarrhœa;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is app. meant by what follows:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease that attacks the stomach, in consequence of which it does not digest the food; becoming in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state, and not retaining the food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n13760","headword_ar":"ذَرِبٌ","root":"*rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K;) applied to anything, (S, M,) as, for instance, a sword, (S,) or a spearhead; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*oruwbN","text_ar":"مَذْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or this latter, applied to a spear-head [&c.], signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ar~abN","text_ar":"مُذَرَّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ar~abN","text_ar":"مُذَرَّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*oruwbN","text_ar":"مَذْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,) applied to a sword (T, M, A, K) and a spearhead, (A, TA,) signify [or signify also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poisoned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steeped in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imbued with, poison,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then sharpened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N *aribN","text_ar":"سُمٌّ ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp poison."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A.) A rájiz says, (referring to cattle, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"dab~ato EalayohaA *aribaAtu AlA^anobaAro"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon which have crept insects resembling ticks, that produce swellings where they creep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp in stinging."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN *aribN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tongue sharp in the extremity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) Tropically, (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sharp tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*oruwbN","text_ar":"مَذْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eloquent, tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a profuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorous, tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obscene, tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribu All~isaAni","text_ar":"ذَرِبُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp in tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorous, therein; long-tongued:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariba","text_ar":"ذَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, in tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás [Th], TA:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont to revile;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, in tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, T, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who cares not what he says."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharptongued:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long-tongued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, in tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribapN","text_ar":"ذَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman; (AZ, T, S, A, Msb; *) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irobapN","text_ar":"ذِرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, T, S, M, K:) this last [is app. a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribapN","text_ar":"ذَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and used by poetic license: it] is applied by a rájiz to his wife, (T, S, *) as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, and unfaithful to her husband in respect of her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroj","text_ar":"فَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to Sh, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long-tongued;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, in speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*oruwbN","text_ar":"مَذْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise, accord. to Sh, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, in speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urobN","text_ar":"ذُرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is irreg.; (TA;) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp in tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: (K:) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irobapN","text_ar":"ذِرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*irabN","text_ar":"ذِرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S, M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEidapN *aribapN","text_ar":"مَعِدَةٌ ذَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stomach sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keen, by reason of hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribato maEidatuhu","text_ar":"ذَرِبَتْ مَعِدَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and also, the contr., i. e.] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stomach in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jurHN *aribN","text_ar":"جُرحٌ ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wound in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state, and wide, and not admitting of cure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiyd","text_ar":"صَدِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ichor tinged with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribu Alxuluqi","text_ar":"ذَرِبُ الخُلُقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, natural disposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*arobN","text_ar":"ذَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","T","A","TA","K","Msb","AZ"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}